text: Found out that a new malay food stall is open daily mon-fri. Breakfast is serve also such as fried bee hoon, fried kway teow, nasi lemak, lontong, and fried rice for breakfast. For lunch will be nasi padang mon-thurs. Alot of variety to choose from. Friday will be a little special nasi biryani is serve here. Price is cheap portion is alot and most importantly it is very nicee!! Must try when u are there!!

is a convenient place. same building as my office. However, the number of customers may be to small for the stalls to be viable. Food variety quite limited.
The stallholders try selling different food, but unfortunately as mentioned earlier, customers base too small to make business sustainable...
Great new place for a Kopi break.  Newly renovated.  Bright & cool.  Great cup of teh shu tai from their $M automated kopitiam machine.  Gonna try their nasi lamak (looks really good) next week 😁
Nice newly renovated cafe with great ambience and variety of food at great value. Definitely the place to stop by to grab some breakfast or lunch during workdays.
Super nice and cozy place to take a break from the daily busy schedule or have a quick bite and not forgetting the yummy selections from the stores... Price of food 👍 Ambient 😍. Overall 🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟.
